          <h1 id="u79846-2">JET BOATING </h1>
       </div>   
       <div class="clearfix colelem" id="pu79797-13"><!-- group -->

        </div>
        <!-- /m_editable -->
        <div class="ASM---p---body-text clearfix grpelem shared_content left-block-1" id="u79797-13" data-muse-uid="U79797" data-muse-type="txt_frame" data-ibe-flags="txtStyleSrc" data-content-guid="u79797-13_content"><!-- content -->
         <p id="u79797-2">This is one of Montréal 's most exhilarating and exciting activity for people of all ages. Jet Boating is a symbol of the spirit, history, fun and adventure that makes Montréal unique. Ride on the boat called “Saute Moutons”, through the last rapids on the St. Lawrence, the river which gave birth to this great city. Tales of Champlain and Indian guides descending the rapids in birch bark canoes are a part of all history books. From the lumberjacks who rode the log rafts to those who were on the steamships, all admit that shooting the rapids was sheer excitement. </p>
         <p id="u79797-3">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-5">You’ll be fully geared-up with a raincoat, rain pants and rubber “booties” because you’ll get wet! A truly one-of a kind, unique experience. </p>
         <p id="u79797-6">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-8">Returning to the dock, but a stone’s throw away from Old Montréal, you will sample some of the city’s finest culinary delights, before returning to the Hotel.</p>
         <p id="u79797-9">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-11">Duration of tour, including lunch: 4 hours  </p>


