          <h1 id="u79846-2">CYCLING ALONG THE LACHINE CANAL</h1>
       </div>   
       <div class="clearfix colelem" id="pu79797-13"><!-- group -->

        </div>
        <!-- /m_editable -->
        <div class="ASM---p---body-text clearfix grpelem shared_content left-block-1" id="u79797-13" data-muse-uid="U79797" data-muse-type="txt_frame" data-ibe-flags="txtStyleSrc" data-content-guid="u79797-13_content"><!-- content -->
         <p id="u79797-2">Montréal is known for its “bike friendly” streets and paths. As you peddle your way around Montréal, your knowledgeable guide will explain various things you will see along the way. The diversified architecture, the quaint neighborhoods as well as unique bike paths on the neighboring islands; all this will allow you to truly experience Montréal  in a unique way. </p>
         <p id="u79797-3">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-5">Depart from Old Montréal accompanied by a professional guide and discover up close yet another side of Montréal. With direct access to a bicycle path network of over 350 kms of picturesque views . . . you will sample the highlights of what these routes have to offer and see Montréal in a whole new light! Along the way, stop in an authentic restaurant for lunch to sample some of Montréal’s culinary delights.</p>
         <p id="u79797-6">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-8">Duration of tour, including lunch: 4 hours </p>


