        <div class="ASM-h3-Subheading clearfix colelem shared_content" id="u79846-4" data-muse-uid="U79846" data-muse-type="txt_frame" data-IBE-flags="txtStyleSrc" data-content-guid="u79846-4_content" style="width:569px;margin-left:0"><!-- content -->
          <h1 id="u79846-2">SKY VENTURE</h1>
       </div>   
       <div class="clearfix colelem" id="pu79797-13"><!-- group -->

        </div>
        <!-- /m_editable -->
        <div class="ASM---p---body-text clearfix grpelem shared_content left-block-1" id="u79797-13" data-muse-uid="U79797" data-muse-type="txt_frame" data-ibe-flags="txtStyleSrc" data-content-guid="u79797-13_content"><!-- content -->
         <p id="u79797-2">Come and defy the laws of gravity in the only recirculating indoor freefall simulator in Canada.  It's an opportunity to experience the sensation of free-fall – without jumping out of an airplane. Imagine a 14 foot cylindrical diameter vertical tube that is 45 feet tall in which the airstream is passing at a speed of 175 km per hour. Once inside the wind tunnel, you will have a real sense of what skydivers experience during the free-fall portion of their jump, which is generally done from 13 500 to 3 500 feet of altitude at a speed of 200 km an hour. All of that in an environment so secure that it is even accessible to children aged of 4 years and older.

 </p>
         <p id="u79797-3">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-5">The concept of experiencing the free-fall indoors dates back to the 1960s and has followed a steady evolution until 1998, the year of introduction of the first generation of the vertical wind tunnel. It has since operated with great success and exceptional reliability. A team composed of 4 instructors were soon able to prove how accurate the simulator is after they won an important free-fall competition just from training in the wind tunnel and having only done a few actual jumps. Since then, all competing teams train in vertical wind tunnels. This is truly a once-in-a-lifetime experience! </p>
         <p id="u79797-6">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-8">As a fitting end to this amazing experience, lunch will be served at a local restaurant.

</p>
         <p id="u79797-9">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-11">Duration of tour, including lunch: 4 hours </p>


