        <div class="ASM-h3-Subheading clearfix colelem shared_content" id="u79846-4" data-muse-uid="U79846" data-muse-type="txt_frame" data-IBE-flags="txtStyleSrc" data-content-guid="u79846-4_content" style="width:569px;margin-left:0"><!-- content -->
          <h1 id="u79846-2">MAISON CHRISTIAN FAURE PASTRY WORKSHOP & LUNCH </h1>
       </div>   
       <div class="clearfix colelem" id="pu79797-13"><!-- group -->

        </div>
        <!-- /m_editable -->
        <div class="ASM---p---body-text clearfix grpelem shared_content left-block-1" id="u79797-13" data-muse-uid="U79797" data-muse-type="txt_frame" data-ibe-flags="txtStyleSrc" data-content-guid="u79797-13_content"><!-- content -->
         <p id="u79797-2">Led by internationally renowned Chef Christian Faure, in the pastry school’s classroom, this activity consists of a simultaneous demonstration and practical team work. Throughout this activity you will discover the techniques behind perfect macarons and learn how to make two delicious fillings as a team. Following each and every step like a real Pastry Chef, you will be able to watch the Chef demonstrate in front of the class as you follow his recipe. During baking time, you will be served a lunch where you will enjoy time with the one and only Chef Christian Faure, Meilleur Ouvrier de France. You will be able to interact with him and share your thoughts and comments about the experience. </p>
         <p id="u79797-3">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-5">Born in Villefranche-sur-Saône, France, Chef Christian Faure M.O.F. studied at Maison Lartaud andthen at the Eculy Dardilly Training Centre in Lyon. Hard working and eager to learn new techniques, his progression was remarkable and he was hired by the venerable Maison Dalloyau Pâtisserie in Paris at the age of 18, before being recruited by Jean Paul Buchet to manage the Pastry Central of the Paris Flô Prestige boutiques. In 1994, Christian was awarded the
Jean-Louis Berthelot Award in the Dessert Plate category. He thereafter took the position of Executive Pastry Chef at the Hotel Royal Riviera Palace. 1997 really marked the consecration of his career when he obtained the supreme title of Meilleur Ouvrier de France Glacier.
 </p>
         <p id="u79797-9">&nbsp;</p>
         <p id="u79797-11">Duration of tour, including lunch: 4 hours  </p>


